12/04/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Two people have been arrested for the kidnapping of former Croat Bosnian presidency member Ante Jelavic, the police announced on Friday (April 10th).
Jelavic's kidnappers released him without collecting a demanded 1m-euro ransom.
In other news, a 44-year-old man on Saturday (April 11th) killed his wife and nine-year-old son and tried to commit suicide afterwards.
The family lived in a western Croatian village.
Police arrested the father, whose motives are unclear.
(Nezavisne Novine;
BTA - 11/04/09;
Jutarnij List, Hina, 24 Sata, HRT - 10/04/09;
AFP, HRT, - 11/04/09)
